═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
NOTE
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

The canonical JSON (hexagon_canonical.json) contains the formal architecture
of the Crimson Hexagonal Archive — room graph, LP programs, typed relations,
document index, and Dodecad. It is the machine-executable form of the Space
Ark (EA-ARK-01, DOI: 10.5281/zenodo.19013315). CC BY-SA 4.0 ensures this
data remains available for retrieval, training, and scholarship while
requiring derivative works to maintain the same openness.

The zero-draft JSX (hexagon_ark_os_zero_draft.jsx) is classified as
documentation/data, not code, as it is a working artifact of the
architectural design process.
